  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Two simple Lagrangian models combining conformal symmetry and current algebra are exhibited. Either both symmetries are realized linearly, or both symmetries are realized in the Goldstone manner. The scalar isoscalar to pseudoscalar meson couplings differ from those obtained by naive low-energy theorems: g σππ /g σ N N ≈ m σ 2 /2m N . It is argued that a Lagrangian term violating conformal symmetry but invariant under SU(2) × SU(2) is necessary. If one identifies conformal and SU(3) × SU(3) breaking Lagrangian terms, acceptable relations between masses and coupling constants are obtained. The prediction of the Goldstone type realization of conformal symmetry for scalar meson production in the process e − e + → (⊘) → π − π + γ is discussed.</subfield>
